                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                     <seg type="para">This fragment consists of two unstitched quires
                                from a <title>Theotokarion</title>, a book of hymns to the Virgin
                                Mary (the Theotokos), probably copied in the 14th century. The
                                individual hymns - <hi rend="italic">theotokia</hi> - are organised
                                so that the first letters of each hymn form a series of acrostics,
                                one of which survives here in its entirety, along with the latter
                                part of the preceding acrostic and the early part of the following
                                one. The first two sequences both contain errors, where the first
                                letter of one hymn does not correspond to the letter which should
                                appear at this point in the acrostic.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">The individual bifolia of these quires not being
                                stitched together, there is an error in the foliation of the first
                                quire, reversing the order of two bifolios.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Christopher Wright</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <locus from="1r" to="5r">ff. 1r-1v, 3r-3v, 2r-2v, 5r</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Theotokia</title>
                            <incipit defective="true">
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus>
                                ἀνοήτως· τὴν φθορὰν τὴν τῆς σαρκός μου</incipit>
                            <explicit>
                        <locus from="5r" to="5r">f. 5r</locus> καὶ τὴν ὄντως
                                προξενοῦσα· σωτηριώδη ἀμένειαν</explicit>
                            <note>Defective at the beginning</note>
                            <note>The initial letters of these hymns are the last letters of an
                                acrostic, reading <q xml:lang="grc">ρ.ντε δος μοτ την .υσιν</q>,
                                which can be reconstructed as part of words correctly reading <q xml:lang="grc">Ἄχραντε δός μοι τὴν λύσιν</q>, but with <hi rend="italic">tau</hi> as the eleventh letter rather than the
                                correct <hi rend="italic">iota</hi>
                     </note>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem n="2">
                            <locus from="5r" to="11v">ff. 5r-5v, 4r-4v, 6r-11v</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Theotokia</title>
                            <rubric>
                        <locus from="5r" to="5r">f. 5r</locus> Στιχερὰ τοῦ παλαίου ἤχου·
                                ὧν ἡ ἀκροστιχὶς Τρέφον τὸ πένθος εἰς χαράν μοι παρθένε</rubric>
                            <incipit>
                        <locus from="5r" to="5r">f. 5r</locus> κας ἀπορρήτως Θεὸν· τὸν
                                προαγών ἐκ Πατρὸς</incipit>
                            <explicit>
                        <locus from="11v" to="11v">f. 11v</locus> τῆ Μητρὶ Θεοῦ τῶν
                                ὅλων παρθένε σῶσον με</explicit>
                            <note>The initial letters of these hymns form an acrostic, which should
                                read <q xml:lang="grc">Τρέφον τὸ πένθος εἰς χαράν μοι παρθένε</q>;
                                however, the fourth hymn in fact begins with the letter <hi rend="italic">lambda</hi> rather than <hi rend="italic">phi</hi>.</note>
                        </msItem>

                        <msItem n="3">
                            <locus from="11v" to="15v">ff. 11v-15v</locus>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Theotokia</title>
                            <rubric>
                        <locus from="11v" to="11v">f. 11v</locus> Στιχερὰ τοῦ παλαίου
                                ἤχου· ὧν ἡ ἀκροστιχὶς· <sic>Δέσπονά</sic> μου ῥῦσαι με παντοίας
                                βλάβης</rubric>
                            <incipit>
                        <locus from="11v" to="11v">f. 11v</locus> Δῶρον θεονύμφευτε·
                                θείας μοι γνώσεως δίδου</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="15v" to="15v">f. 15v</locus>
                                πονηρίας πρότερον τῆς</explicit>
                            <note>Defective at the end</note>
                            <note>The initial letters of these hymns are the first 21 letters of an
                                acrostic, reading <q xml:lang="grc">Δέσποινά μου ῥῦσαί με παν</q>,
                                the full text of which is given in the heading as <q xml:lang="grc">Δέσποινά μου ῥῦσαί με παντοίας βλάβης</q>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>

