                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text was copied in <term type="script">mixed minuscule</term>
                                    script, slanting slightly to the right, in brown ink, with
                                    moderate variation in letter size and some flourishing of tails
                                    into the margin.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations and superscript word endings appear
                                    throughout the line. Breathings are round and mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is absent, or subscript. There is
                                    decorative use of the double dot, and accentuation of all
                                        <foreign xml:lang="la">nomina sacra</foreign>. Accents are
                                    sometimes joined to letters and breathings.</p>
                                <p>The modern <hi rend="italic">eta</hi> and modern <hi rend="italic">nu</hi> are present, and there are inclusions
                                    of letters within <hi rend="italic">omicron</hi>.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the upper and middle points and full
                                    stop.</p>
                                <p>Headings are written in the same style in red ink.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <decoDesc>
                            <decoNote type="colInit">The beginnings of sections are marked by minor
                                initials in red ink.</decoNote>

                            <decoNote type="vignette">The beginning of the text on <locus from="5r" to="5r">f. 5r</locus> is preceded by a simple vignette in red
                                ink.</decoNote>
                        </decoDesc>

                        <additions>
                            <p>There are occasional marginal annotations in Greek by different hands
                                (ff. <locus from="1r" to="1r">1r</locus>, <locus from="11v" to="12v">11v-12v</locus>, <locus from="14r" to="14r">14r</locus>).</p>
                            <p>The fragment has been marked with the present classmark on <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus> and with the present classmark
                                and the former classmark T.26 on <locus from="7r" to="7r">f.
                                    7r</locus>.</p>
                  </additions>
